        "text": "# The Idea of a Myth (Dil wrote this - not necessarily subscribed to by anyone else)\nDeep Governance statements should not be over-prescriptive. They need to be clear enough so that people know whether they should join in, or should leave, but they should aspire to a cloudy, inspirational character that conveys purpose in a mytho-poetic manner.\nThis allows for metaphorical / metaphysical shifts in purpose over time without requiring re-statement.\nAlthough a founding purpose should not ideally be changed (if it needs to change, then its probably better to start a new project without baggage - even fold the old project and have it donate some/all of its assets to the new version) - it does need to settle in.\nThus at the outset, we have an ideation/fluid phase, during which we can develop / refine the statement.\n"
